				<a href="http://www.cbc.ca/story/news/national/2004/12/06/deserter-refugee041206.html" target="_blank">http://www.cbc.ca/story/news/national/2004/12/06/deserter-refugee041206.html</a>
<br />

<br />

<br />
I have a simple question, wouldnt it be more appropriate for our civilised countries to allow an option to such a coward/morally strong person?
<br />

<br />
When I read this case I cant help but think the following should happen:  - The soldier been offer to either face court martial OR be strip of American citizenship(and helped in gaining a Canadian or whatever place seem fine to him).
<br />

<br />
I know the US military need to save face, but exile would cost less money to everyone and make everyone happier.
<br />

<br />
For Canada, it is hard to regulate such a case because althought we agree with the little man ideas in theory, he is also a deserter, unless the US government think it is a necessity to trial this guy, wont an exile and a kind request for Canadian citizenship been an easier and less expensive solution?
<br />

<br />
If this guy is sended back to be in a US jail, some of my RL friends say they will go to NYC and pee on the gift France give you about freedom, althought I found the idea funny, wont it be better to be more human?
<br />

<br />
I dont care if this soldier is a coward or a morally strong person, as far as I am concern, he should be welcome in Canada, he will be a working part of society...Exile sound a more economicly rational solution and a more human solution, and the US military still save the face, he CHOOSE exile over a ''rightfull'' court martial because US allow it.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
